Integrating Hardware VTEPs with VMware NSX-MH Switches running Cumulus Linux can integrate with VMware NSX Multi-Hypervisor (MH) to act as hardware VTEP gateways. The VMware NSX-MH controller provides consistent provisioning across virtual and physical server infrastructures.
{width=&ldquo;500&rdquo;}
Cumulus Linux also supports integration with VMware NSX in high availability mode. Refer to OVSDB Server High Availability.
